    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <opener><dateline><date when="1918-02-15">February 13 1918</dateline></date>
                    <salute>Dear <persName key="harriet_monroe">Harriet:–</persName></salute></opener>
                <p>I should certainly much prefer not to have you put that figure after my name. In fact, I should really rather 
                    not have my name at all if that could be managed. Could you not call it anonymous, or a friend or something.
                    Being a poet myself and being occasionally printed in your paper, I think it looks badly to be also known as 
                    guarantor. Still, if you insist on the name you can have it, but without the figure.   </p>
                
                <closer> Affectionately yours,</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
